highlights.description: Growing up in small town, feeling safe
Discrimination causing other to overlook his intelligence, learning to do away with what others saw him as
Having a sister with Down Syndrome inspiring interest in special ed
personal experience with suicide teaching compassion for others
Madison has an exclusionary way of distributing info through networks, from a mom enrolling a kid in 4K
Affordable housing and college student discussion, spurred by cross-pollination from Hearth
KC: Concerns over neighborhood response to Tree Lane Housing project. Would be good to play in a group expressing concerns over homelessness or affordable housing.
lack of access to knowledge about public resources especially regarding UW
Barriers for people opening up their real perspectives
Curiosity about the variances in lived experience
Belief that the main unheard voices in the community are the youth.
Need to see whole system, and be honest about your desire to live in an inclusive environment.
Even when downtown has a school initiative, it comes off like a "front", for show, since people out at the local level don't know about it.
Even though it cn be intimidating to speak up, alders and board members need to hear citizens speaking up.
